SIMPLE: pyroelectric
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pyroelectric
<hw>Pyr`o*e*lec"tric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pyro-</ets> + <ets>electric</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or dependent on,
pyroelectricity; receiving electric polarity when heated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pyroelectric</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pyroelectric
<hw>Pyr`o*e*lec"tric</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>A
substance which becomes electrically polar when heated, exhibiting
opposite charges of statical electricity at two separate parts,
especially the two extremities.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pyroelectricity</ent>⟦br⟧
